defs.docs:
This crate provides native rust implementations of
 image encoders and decoders and basic image manipulation
 functions.

defs.name: nq
defs.docs:
NEUQUANT Neural-Net quantization algorithm by Anthony Dekker, 1994.
 See "Kohonen neural networks for optimal colour quantization"
 in "Network: Computation in Neural Systems" Vol. 5 (1994) pp 351-367.
 for a discussion of the algorithm.
 See also  http://www.acm.org/~dekker/NEUQUANT.HTML

defs.name: invert
defs.docs:
Invert each pixel within the supplied image.
 This function operates in place.

defs.name: contrast
defs.value: fn <I, P, S> (image: &I, contrast: f32) -> ImageBuffer<P, Vec<S>>
defs.docs:
Adjust the contrast of the supplied image.
 ```contrast``` is the amount to adjust the contrast by.
 Negative values decrease the contrast and positive values increase the contrast.

defs.name: brighten
defs.value: fn <I, P, S> (image: &I, value: i32) -> ImageBuffer<P, Vec<S>>
defs.docs:
Brighten the supplied image.
 ```value``` is the amount to brighten each pixel by.
 Negative values decrease the brightness and positive values increase it.

defs.name: huerotate
defs.value: fn <I, P, S> (image: &I, value: i32) -> ImageBuffer<P, Vec<S>>
defs.docs:
Hue rotate the supplied image.
 `value` is the degrees to rotate each pixel by.
 0 and 360 do nothing, the rest rotates by the given degree value.
 just like the css webkit filter hue-rotate(180)

defs.name: dither

Reduces the colors of the image using the supplied `color_map` while applying

defs.name: resize
defs.value: fn <I> (image: &I, nwidth: u32, nheight: u32, filter: FilterType) -> ImageBuffer<I::Pixel, Vec<<I::Pixel as Pixel>::Subpixel>>

Resize the supplied image to the specified dimensions.

defs.name: width
defs.docs:
Width of decoded image. It could be either scanline length, 
 or scanline count, depending on image orientation.

defs.name: height
defs.docs: Height of decoded image. It depends on orientation too.

defs.name: orientation
defs.docs:
Orientation matrix. For standart orientation it is ((1,0),(0,1)) - left to right, top to bottom.
 First pair tells how resulting pixel coordinates change along a scanline.
 Second pair tells how they change from one scanline to the next.

defs.name: exposure
defs.docs:
Divide color values by exposure to get to get physical radiance in watts/steradian/m^2
 Image may not contain physical data, even if this field is set.

defs.name: color_correction
defs.docs:
Divide color values by corresponing tuple member (r, g, b) to get to get physical radiance in watts/steradian/m^2
 Image may not contain physical data, even if this field is set.

defs.name: pixel_aspect_ratio
defs.docs: Pixel height divided by pixel width

defs.name: custom_attributes
defs.docs:
All lines contained in image header are put here. Ordering of lines is preserved.
 Lines in the form "key=value" are represented as ("key", "value").
 All other lines are ("", "line")
